1
00:00:01,459 --> 00:00:03,670
[Marcus, in English] <i>All units,</i>
<i>gather at the main exit points.</i>

2
00:00:03,753 --> 00:00:04,921
[in English] <i>We move out in two minutes.</i>

3
00:00:05,755 --> 00:00:07,298
There's someone injured there.

4
00:00:07,382 --> 00:00:09,968
[Marcus] <i>Let us send</i>
<i>one person there to treat them.</i>

5
00:00:10,051 --> 00:00:12,846
<i>He'll just treat the wounded</i>
<i>victim inside there.</i>

6
00:00:12,929 --> 00:00:14,264
[in English] Waiting
for your confirmation.

7
00:00:14,347 --> 00:00:16,182
- Okay, we agree.
- Yes.

8
00:00:16,266 --> 00:00:17,517
[Espina] <i>I'll go in.</i>

9
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:20,437
[in English] The kidnappers
will release our daughter.

10
00:00:21,020 --> 00:00:22,439
[Lydia, in English] <i>And we will surrender.</i>

11
00:00:22,522 --> 00:00:23,815
[Benny] <i>I'm sorry.</i>

12
00:00:23,898 --> 00:00:26,735
[Manuel] Lara, where is it?

13
00:00:26,818 --> 00:00:29,446
- Madam, what's going on with you?!
- [whimpering]

14
00:00:31,823 --> 00:00:33,616
- [clicks]
- [explosion]

15
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:34,451
[Datu Rahman] Jalil!

16
00:00:35,702 --> 00:00:36,661
[explosion]

17
00:00:36,745 --> 00:00:38,747
- [Peter] Doc! Doc!
- [sobs] Marcus…

18
00:00:38,830 --> 00:00:39,998
[people clamoring]

19
00:00:40,081 --> 00:00:42,917
[Manuel, in English] <i>Good job, Lara.</i>

20
00:00:43,001 --> 00:00:44,419
[in English] <i>Good job!</i>

21
00:00:44,961 --> 00:00:46,087
[Marcus] Espina!

22
00:00:47,130 --> 00:00:50,383
Brother, wake up! I'm here. Wake up!

23
00:00:50,467 --> 00:00:51,301
‪[tense music playing]

24
00:00:55,555 --> 00:00:57,432
[both crying]

25
00:00:58,933 --> 00:01:00,060
[Datu Rahman] <i>Omar,</i>
<i>I'm going to the hospital.</i>

26
00:01:00,143 --> 00:01:02,020
<i>I can't leave my son.</i>

27
00:01:02,103 --> 00:01:04,439
We can't go to your son at the hospital

28
00:01:04,522 --> 00:01:06,316
while he's still pretending to be Espina.

29
00:01:06,399 --> 00:01:10,195
He'll be exposed as Jalil
if we go to the hospital.

30
00:01:10,278 --> 00:01:13,031
We don't know how to contact your family.

31
00:01:13,114 --> 00:01:14,032
[Espina] <i>They're far away.</i>

32
00:01:14,115 --> 00:01:15,200
<i>They won't be able to come here either.</i>

33
00:01:15,283 --> 00:01:17,660
Marcus and I will take care
of you for now.

34
00:01:17,744 --> 00:01:20,538
Major Espina, good thing
you're already in stable condition.

35
00:01:20,622 --> 00:01:22,832
And you too, Agent Reyes,

36
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:24,167
I'm glad you're safe.

37
00:01:28,838 --> 00:01:31,508
[mysterious theme music playing]

38
00:01:46,189 --> 00:01:47,482
[morose music playing]

39
00:01:52,112 --> 00:01:53,780
A whole bus full of people died!

40
00:01:54,572 --> 00:01:57,283
We didn't even manage
to save a single one!

41
00:01:57,367 --> 00:01:58,701
I feel bad for Mr. Konno.

42
00:01:59,494 --> 00:02:01,996
He saw his wife and daughter explode.

43
00:02:02,580 --> 00:02:04,666
It looks like that really
was the hostage takers' plan.

44
00:02:04,749 --> 00:02:06,793
But we didn't know
they were going to do that.

45
00:02:06,876 --> 00:02:08,795
We really had no control
over the situation.

46
00:02:09,587 --> 00:02:11,089
I wonder how Major Espina is doing.

47
00:02:11,172 --> 00:02:12,298
I hope he's okay.

48
00:02:13,216 --> 00:02:15,051
Marcus just called earlier.

49
00:02:16,052 --> 00:02:17,762
He said Major Espina has woken up.

50
00:02:18,805 --> 00:02:19,848
That's good.

51
00:02:24,894 --> 00:02:26,604
Where is Agent Angeles?

52
00:02:26,688 --> 00:02:30,441
I need a report
on what happened earlier, ASAP!

53
00:02:30,525 --> 00:02:34,237
Sir, we haven't seen her
since we returned from the mission.

54
00:02:34,946 --> 00:02:35,947
[in English] Goddammit!

55
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:38,867
- [door clicks open]
- [Azuelo, in English] Goddammit!

56
00:02:40,785 --> 00:02:41,828
- Buster!
- [Buster] Sir?

57
00:02:41,911 --> 00:02:43,246
Where is Agent Angeles?

58
00:02:43,329 --> 00:02:44,247
I don't know, sir.

59
00:02:44,330 --> 00:02:47,041
She got off the tactical van
before the bus exploded.

60
00:02:47,125 --> 00:02:49,419
Then she didn't come back.
I thought she was already here.

61
00:02:49,502 --> 00:02:51,629
[pensive music playing]

62
00:02:51,713 --> 00:02:54,048
[scoffs]

63
00:03:01,347 --> 00:03:04,392
<i>The national police headquarters</i>
<i>has confirmed</i>

64
00:03:04,475 --> 00:03:07,937
<i>that there were no survivors</i>
<i>from the tourist bus explosion</i>

65
00:03:08,021 --> 00:03:09,856
<i>on San Aurelio Street.</i>

66
00:03:09,939 --> 00:03:13,234
<i>The couple who took</i>
<i>the hostages were killed,</i>

67
00:03:13,318 --> 00:03:15,653
<i>along with 15 Japanese tourists,</i>

68
00:03:15,737 --> 00:03:18,072
<i>including the wife and daughter</i>

69
00:03:18,156 --> 00:03:21,367
<i>of Japanese delegate Mr. Tatsuo Konno.</i>

70
00:03:21,451 --> 00:03:23,494
[in Japanese] This is horrible!

71
00:03:25,872 --> 00:03:27,290
[in English] I am pulling out everything.

72
00:03:28,541 --> 00:03:29,876
[in English] The deal is dead.

73
00:03:31,044 --> 00:03:33,588
[in Japanese] Because of
this godforsaken country,

74
00:03:34,255 --> 00:03:39,886
my wife and my daughter are gone!

75
00:03:41,304 --> 00:03:42,430
[sobs]

76
00:03:43,514 --> 00:03:45,975
[in English] This is all your fault!

77
00:03:46,684 --> 00:03:50,605
[in Japanese] <i>Also killed in the blast</i>

78
00:03:50,688 --> 00:03:54,817
<i>were the hostage-takers,</i>

79
00:03:54,901 --> 00:03:58,404
<i>married couple Benny and Lydia Santerva,</i>

80
00:03:58,488 --> 00:03:59,906
<i>who reportedly staged</i>
<i>the attack in protest</i>

81
00:03:59,989 --> 00:04:01,491
<i>of a multibillion-dollar investment deal.</i>

82
00:04:01,574 --> 00:04:04,077
<i>Unfortunately, the local elite group</i>

83
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:05,954
<i>known as Task Force Alpha</i>

84
00:04:06,037 --> 00:04:09,874
<i>failed to rescue the hostages</i>

85
00:04:09,958 --> 00:04:13,336
<i>before the vehicle detonated.</i>

86
00:04:13,419 --> 00:04:14,337
BENNY AND LYDIA WERE ALSO KILLED
IN AN EXPLOSION

87
00:04:14,420 --> 00:04:16,756
[in English] <i>The bus hijacking incident</i>
<i>in Manila</i>

88
00:04:16,839 --> 00:04:19,384
<i>has met the worst possible end.</i>

89
00:04:19,467 --> 00:04:22,011
<i>What was supposed to be</i>
<i>a celebratory summit</i>

90
00:04:22,095 --> 00:04:26,391
<i>has instantly turned</i>
<i>into a major diplomatic tragedy.</i>

91
00:04:26,474 --> 00:04:29,727
<i>This catastrophic security failure</i>
<i>cements global concerns</i>

92
00:04:29,811 --> 00:04:32,939
<i>that the Philippines remains</i>
<i>an incompetent,</i>

93
00:04:33,022 --> 00:04:34,774
<i>unsafe place after all.</i>

94
00:04:35,775 --> 00:04:37,110
<i>TFA, what's going on?!</i>

95
00:04:37,193 --> 00:04:38,027
GOSH, THE EXPLOSION WAS TERRIBLE!

96
00:04:38,111 --> 00:04:38,987
<i>What is this?!</i>

97
00:04:39,070 --> 00:04:40,488
<i>I thought everything was okay!</i>

98
00:04:40,571 --> 00:04:42,323
<i>I thought everything was under control</i>

99
00:04:42,407 --> 00:04:45,368
<i>after that school shooting incident!</i>

100
00:04:45,451 --> 00:04:47,537
<i>Was that just luck?</i>

101
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:48,955
[in English] <i>Hit and miss?</i>

102
00:04:49,038 --> 00:04:50,790
[in English] <i>Seventeen casualties.</i>

103
00:04:50,873 --> 00:04:53,876
<i>We're talking about 17 lives here.</i>

104
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:54,836
<i>You messed this up</i>

105
00:04:54,919 --> 00:04:57,922
<i>because of your negligence</i>
<i>and incompetence, TFA!</i>

106
00:04:58,006 --> 00:04:59,966
<i>Are you even thinking?!</i>

107
00:05:00,049 --> 00:05:01,801
<i>The whole world is condemning us</i>

108
00:05:01,884 --> 00:05:03,845
<i>because of your negligence!</i>

109
00:05:04,846 --> 00:05:06,639
<i>Get yourselves together!</i>

110
00:05:06,723 --> 00:05:08,099
- <i>Oh my, Mama Loi!</i>
- <i>Oh?</i>

111
00:05:08,182 --> 00:05:10,685
<i>This is insane! Did you guys see the news?</i>

112
00:05:10,768 --> 00:05:13,146
<i>Oh! You mean the bus that got blown up?</i>

113
00:05:13,229 --> 00:05:14,105
[Ogie] <i>Oh, yeah!</i>

114
00:05:14,188 --> 00:05:15,982
<i>The one full of Japanese tourists?</i>

115
00:05:16,065 --> 00:05:18,985
- <i>Exactly.</i>
- <i>It's so heartbreaking!</i>

116
00:05:19,068 --> 00:05:20,987
<i>I feel so bad for them.</i>

117
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:23,531
<i>Ugh, it really gave me a headache.</i>

118
00:05:23,614 --> 00:05:24,866
<i>Just imagine</i>

119
00:05:24,949 --> 00:05:27,410
<i>how many people were inside that bus,</i>

120
00:05:27,493 --> 00:05:29,912
<i>and they were just killed like that!</i>

121
00:05:29,996 --> 00:05:34,792
<i>Exactly, Ogie, Mama Loi.</i>
<i>They all had families.</i>

122
00:05:34,876 --> 00:05:36,085
<i>It's just so tragic.</i>

123
00:05:36,169 --> 00:05:38,629
<i>Wow, Brena was right.</i>

124
00:05:38,713 --> 00:05:40,006
<i>You're absolutely right, Brena.</i>

125
00:05:40,089 --> 00:05:41,215
[clicking tongue]

126
00:05:41,299 --> 00:05:43,092
- <i>Oh, wait, Ogie.</i>
- <i>Oh?</i>

127
00:05:43,176 --> 00:05:45,636
<i>What's going to happen</i>
<i>to the Japanese investors now?</i>

128
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:46,679
<i>Oh, what about them?</i>

129
00:05:46,763 --> 00:05:48,514
<i>Well, one of their conditions</i>

130
00:05:48,598 --> 00:05:50,933
- <i>before investing in our country</i>
- <i>Oh.</i>

131
00:05:51,017 --> 00:05:53,311
<i>was that the Philippines</i>
<i>had to be peaceful</i>

132
00:05:53,394 --> 00:05:55,438
<i>and that the spread of illegal firearms</i>

133
00:05:55,521 --> 00:05:57,690
<i>had to be brought under control.</i>

134
00:05:57,774 --> 00:06:01,235
<i>Then they're probably not going</i>
<i>through with it anymore.</i>

135
00:06:01,319 --> 00:06:03,071
- [Mama Loi] <i>Oh!</i>
- <i>Yes! Yes!</i>

136
00:06:03,154 --> 00:06:04,614
<i>I mean, can you believe</i>

137
00:06:04,697 --> 00:06:07,909
<i>their own fellow countrymen</i>
<i>were the ones targeted?</i>

138
00:06:07,992 --> 00:06:11,537
<i>So the people who were hoping to get jobs</i>

139
00:06:11,621 --> 00:06:13,956
<i>because of that investment</i>
<i>are out of luck too?</i>

140
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:18,419
<i>Most likely!</i>

141
00:06:18,503 --> 00:06:21,089
<i>And of course, our fellow</i>
<i>Filipinos working abroad</i>

142
00:06:21,172 --> 00:06:23,299
<i>will be affected too.</i>

143
00:06:23,382 --> 00:06:27,720
<i>I mean, what must the rest</i>
<i>of the world think of them now?</i>

144
00:06:27,804 --> 00:06:29,055
[tongue clicking]

145
00:06:29,138 --> 00:06:31,516
<i>It's really heartbreaking.</i>

146
00:06:31,599 --> 00:06:34,393
<i>To all the families who lost</i>
<i>their loved ones</i>

147
00:06:34,477 --> 00:06:35,853
<i>in this tragedy,</i>

148
00:06:35,937 --> 00:06:38,773
<i>we extend our deepest condolences.</i>

149
00:06:38,856 --> 00:06:42,360
<i>We don't know when</i>
<i>all this violence will end,</i>

150
00:06:42,443 --> 00:06:45,613
<i>but we continue to pray</i>

151
00:06:45,696 --> 00:06:48,324
<i>that it finally comes to an end</i>

152
00:06:48,407 --> 00:06:51,869
<i>and that justice will be served.</i>

153
00:06:52,870 --> 00:06:54,956
<i>Meanwhile,</i>

154
00:06:55,039 --> 00:06:57,750
<i>Police Major Allan Espina</i>

155
00:06:57,834 --> 00:07:00,419
<i>remains injured and is still</i>
<i>recovering in the hospital.</i>

156
00:07:00,503 --> 00:07:02,255
<i>He was supposed to board the bus</i>

157
00:07:02,338 --> 00:07:05,591
<i>to treat one of the wounded hostages.</i>

158
00:07:05,675 --> 00:07:07,218
- [reporter] Sir, what's the truth?
- [clamoring]

159
00:07:07,301 --> 00:07:08,678
What really happened, sir?

160
00:07:08,761 --> 00:07:13,266
- Should we blame the government?
- [in English] Wait! Please! Please!

161
00:07:13,349 --> 00:07:14,267
Let's not

162
00:07:14,350 --> 00:07:17,186
blame the government.

163
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:22,108
<i>The NLEA, the SID, Task Force Alpha,</i>

164
00:07:22,191 --> 00:07:24,819
<i>the entire operating system,</i>
<i>did everything they could.</i>

165
00:07:25,403 --> 00:07:26,904
But there are--

166
00:07:26,988 --> 00:07:29,365
But there are just people

167
00:07:29,449 --> 00:07:31,200
willing to destroy everything

168
00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:33,786
for their own agenda.

169
00:07:33,870 --> 00:07:36,289
[tense music playing]

170
00:07:42,003 --> 00:07:43,379
- [exhales sharply, in English] Excuse me!
- [clamoring]

171
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:45,173
[in English] Excuse me!

172
00:07:59,937 --> 00:08:01,439
[Azuelo] You bastard.

173
00:08:02,940 --> 00:08:05,193
You've been playing with all of us.

174
00:08:09,697 --> 00:08:10,531
‪[dramatic sting]

175
00:08:13,951 --> 00:08:15,077
‪[sinister music playing]

176
00:08:16,078 --> 00:08:17,121
[knocking on door]

177
00:08:17,205 --> 00:08:18,039
[door clicks open]

178
00:08:22,084 --> 00:08:23,085
Sir.

179
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:28,090
Let's say you're right, Reyes.

180
00:08:29,217 --> 00:08:32,386
If Carillo is really behind all of this,

181
00:08:33,513 --> 00:08:34,388
who are his accomplices?

182
00:08:34,472 --> 00:08:35,306
‪[tense music playing]

183
00:08:39,519 --> 00:08:41,103
I can't say yet, sir.

184
00:08:51,239 --> 00:08:54,742
Do you think Agent Angeles…

185
00:08:55,868 --> 00:08:57,495
had something to do with this?

186
00:08:57,578 --> 00:08:59,956
Is that why she still hasn't shown up?

187
00:09:03,584 --> 00:09:05,253
I'm not sure yet, sir.

188
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:10,299
- But that's my suspicion.
- [dramatic sting]

189
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:21,644
[Jamilah] Jalil…

190
00:09:26,941 --> 00:09:27,900
[Jamilah crying]

191
00:09:27,984 --> 00:09:28,901
[Jalil] Jamilah.

192
00:09:28,985 --> 00:09:30,570
[crying] Jalil!

193
00:09:30,653 --> 00:09:32,822
[somber music playing]

194
00:09:34,907 --> 00:09:37,952
[sobs] Jalil…

195
00:09:38,035 --> 00:09:40,037
I was scared.

196
00:09:40,121 --> 00:09:43,207
When I saw what happened to the bus,

197
00:09:43,291 --> 00:09:44,625
I was worried about you.

198
00:09:44,709 --> 00:09:46,502
I didn't know what happened to you.

199
00:09:47,503 --> 00:09:49,338
And it's hard because…

200
00:09:50,089 --> 00:09:52,216
I couldn't even reach out to you.

201
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:54,385
I couldn't even hug you.

202
00:09:55,386 --> 00:10:00,766
[sniffles] Because they might
find out your real identity.

203
00:10:00,850 --> 00:10:04,812
[crying]

204
00:10:09,984 --> 00:10:11,611
I'm sorry, Jamilah.

205
00:10:11,694 --> 00:10:13,195
[Jamilah sobbing]

206
00:10:13,279 --> 00:10:14,947
This will all end soon.

207
00:10:16,157 --> 00:10:17,199
[sobs]

208
00:10:17,908 --> 00:10:19,493
I understand. [sniffles]

209
00:10:20,786 --> 00:10:23,080
I only worry about your condition.

210
00:10:25,416 --> 00:10:27,043
Jalil…

211
00:10:28,711 --> 00:10:32,340
I'm staying strong because of you.

212
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:35,593
[Jamilah crying]

213
00:10:36,927 --> 00:10:39,180
[Jalil] Jamilah… [sniffles]

214
00:10:39,263 --> 00:10:40,097
‪[sobbing]

215
00:10:42,308 --> 00:10:43,643
Jalil, please.

216
00:10:44,685 --> 00:10:46,687
You should be careful too.

217
00:10:46,771 --> 00:10:49,565
You always get hurt.

218
00:10:53,486 --> 00:10:56,614
That's why I'm lucky

219
00:10:56,697 --> 00:10:58,157
because my sister is a nurse…

220
00:11:00,451 --> 00:11:02,495
who always takes care of me.

221
00:11:03,079 --> 00:11:05,915
Ouch! That hurts, Jamilah.

222
00:11:05,998 --> 00:11:07,291
I'm really sorry.

223
00:11:07,375 --> 00:11:09,752
But don't worry.

224
00:11:09,835 --> 00:11:12,213
When I grow up, I'll become a nurse,

225
00:11:12,296 --> 00:11:14,048
so there will be someone to treat you

226
00:11:14,131 --> 00:11:15,466
whenever you get hurt.

227
00:11:16,050 --> 00:11:17,927
[Jamilah] My goodness. [sobs]

228
00:11:18,010 --> 00:11:21,472
You're still joking
when you already look like that.

229
00:11:26,602 --> 00:11:28,104
Brother…

230
00:11:28,187 --> 00:11:30,481
I have to go.

231
00:11:31,732 --> 00:11:34,151
Recover first, please. [sniffles]

232
00:11:34,819 --> 00:11:35,903
Okay?

233
00:11:35,986 --> 00:11:37,988
I'll get going then.

234
00:11:38,072 --> 00:11:40,157
[sniffling] Get well.

235
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:44,829
- I'll go now.
- Jamilah…

236
00:11:48,332 --> 00:11:49,542
[in Tausug] Thank you.

237
00:11:51,627 --> 00:11:53,254
For everything.

238
00:11:55,714 --> 00:11:57,758
- Be strong.
- Mm-hmm.

239
00:12:00,928 --> 00:12:02,179
[in Tausug] Thank you.

240
00:12:02,263 --> 00:12:04,723
[somber music playing]

241
00:12:10,229 --> 00:12:12,189
[Jamilah sniffles]

242
00:12:18,904 --> 00:12:21,824
[breathes deeply]

243
00:12:43,888 --> 00:12:47,975
[stirring music playing]

244
00:12:51,103 --> 00:12:52,813
[clamoring, shouting]

245
00:12:52,897 --> 00:12:53,731
[young Lara] Mommy!

246
00:12:53,814 --> 00:12:54,857
[crying]

247
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:57,067
- [young Lara crying] <i>Mommy! Daddy!</i>
- [explosions]

248
00:12:57,151 --> 00:12:58,110
<i>Daddy!</i>

249
00:13:00,613 --> 00:13:02,031
<i>Mommy!</i>

250
00:13:02,615 --> 00:13:04,116
<i>Mommy! Daddy!</i>

251
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:05,618
<i>Mommy!</i>

252
00:13:05,701 --> 00:13:06,994
- [morose music playing]
- [dramatic whoosh]

253
00:13:10,206 --> 00:13:13,626
[Lara] Why did they have to die, Dad?
Why did they die?

254
00:13:14,710 --> 00:13:17,546
[Lara] <i>Oliver, Patrick,</i>
<i>Russell, and Harold.</i>

255
00:13:18,297 --> 00:13:21,550
<i>The civilians on the island.</i>
<i>They were innocent.</i>

256
00:13:21,634 --> 00:13:23,302
<i>Why did they have to die?</i>

257
00:13:26,305 --> 00:13:27,139
‪[dramatic whoosh]

258
00:13:32,811 --> 00:13:33,812
[whimpers]

259
00:13:33,896 --> 00:13:35,314
[Lara] <i>What are we doing, Felix?</i>

260
00:13:35,397 --> 00:13:36,982
Are we still doing the right thing?

261
00:13:37,900 --> 00:13:39,443
Why are there kids getting involved?

262
00:13:39,527 --> 00:13:40,819
Why did they need to be dragged into this?

263
00:13:40,903 --> 00:13:42,404
Why did children need to be involved here?

264
00:13:44,073 --> 00:13:46,367
[Lara] <i>I don't know</i>
<i>if I'm still doing the right thing.</i>

265
00:13:47,701 --> 00:13:49,912
A lot of people are getting involved.

266
00:13:50,412 --> 00:13:51,539
Even children.

267
00:13:51,622 --> 00:13:52,873
[sobs]

268
00:13:56,418 --> 00:13:59,588
I'm turning into the people
who killed my parents.

269
00:13:59,672 --> 00:14:04,552
Lara, whatever General tells us to do,

270
00:14:04,635 --> 00:14:07,555
that's what we'll do
because that's the right thing to do.

271
00:14:07,638 --> 00:14:09,431
[crying]

272
00:14:12,351 --> 00:14:14,812
[young girl crying]

273
00:14:15,896 --> 00:14:19,525
Mommy…

274
00:14:24,363 --> 00:14:25,990
‪-[dramatic whoosh]
‪-[explosion]

275
00:14:27,533 --> 00:14:29,451
- [morose music continues]
- [sniffles]

276
00:14:30,286 --> 00:14:33,664
[phone ringing]

277
00:14:37,042 --> 00:14:38,377
[whimpers]

278
00:14:39,086 --> 00:14:40,129
‪[panicked breath]

279
00:14:41,964 --> 00:14:43,340
[phone rings]

280
00:14:43,424 --> 00:14:47,720
[line ringing]

281
00:14:50,347 --> 00:14:51,181
‪[phone ringing]

282
00:14:54,268 --> 00:14:55,102
‪[line ringing]

283
00:14:58,272 --> 00:14:59,106
‪[phone ringing]

284
00:15:03,903 --> 00:15:04,904
[phone thuds]

285
00:15:04,987 --> 00:15:06,196
‪[somber music playing]

286
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:13,954
[line disconnected beeping]

287
00:15:29,845 --> 00:15:31,847
‪[music intensifies, fades]

288
00:15:34,308 --> 00:15:35,976
We have failed to do our mission.

289
00:15:36,602 --> 00:15:39,355
[grim music playing]

290
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:43,984
A lot of people were killed.

291
00:15:47,404 --> 00:15:50,115
We almost lost Major Espina too.

292
00:15:51,116 --> 00:15:53,285
[Marcus breathes deeply]

293
00:15:53,369 --> 00:15:54,703
We lost today.

294
00:15:55,287 --> 00:15:59,917
[inhales] But that's more reason why
we need to not lose morale.

295
00:16:01,585 --> 00:16:04,046
Because in the following days,

296
00:16:04,129 --> 00:16:07,341
we will face even bigger challenges.

297
00:16:07,925 --> 00:16:09,718
Because what happened earlier…

298
00:16:12,429 --> 00:16:16,809
will create more chaos for all of us.

299
00:16:16,892 --> 00:16:18,435
Remember that.

300
00:16:20,020 --> 00:16:21,814
We have to be prepared.

301
00:16:25,484 --> 00:16:26,902
[in English] Understood?

302
00:16:29,822 --> 00:16:31,115
[in unison, in English] Yes, sir!

303
00:16:45,379 --> 00:16:47,339
[morose music playing]

304
00:16:47,423 --> 00:16:48,465
Mother.

305
00:16:49,049 --> 00:16:50,300
- Mother.
- Oh, son!

306
00:16:51,010 --> 00:16:52,052
- My son…
- Oh.

307
00:16:53,971 --> 00:16:55,848
[sniffs]

308
00:16:55,931 --> 00:16:58,684
I'm glad you're not hurt.

309
00:16:59,601 --> 00:17:00,769
[Usman] I'll all right, Mother.

310
00:17:01,353 --> 00:17:02,521
I didn't get hurt.

311
00:17:02,604 --> 00:17:03,689
Mother, where's the child?

312
00:17:04,273 --> 00:17:07,151
Oh, I let her sleep in my room.

313
00:17:07,901 --> 00:17:10,487
- You know, Usman, I'm worried.
- [music intensifies]

314
00:17:10,571 --> 00:17:13,949
I don't think her parents
were really terrorists.

315
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:17,703
But I think her abduction
has something to do with

316
00:17:17,786 --> 00:17:20,956
Benny and Lydia taking hostages.

317
00:17:22,041 --> 00:17:23,250
Yes, Mother.

318
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:25,377
Your suspicion might be correct.

319
00:17:27,421 --> 00:17:28,839
You know…

320
00:17:28,922 --> 00:17:31,133
I feel very sorry for the child.

321
00:17:31,216 --> 00:17:32,342
She was crying a lot.

322
00:17:33,010 --> 00:17:35,095
So I was thinking about…

323
00:17:36,096 --> 00:17:37,723
fostering her here for now

324
00:17:37,806 --> 00:17:40,225
because there's no one left
to take care of her.

325
00:17:42,019 --> 00:17:43,604
All right, Mother.

326
00:17:44,229 --> 00:17:45,397
I also think that's right.

327
00:17:45,939 --> 00:17:47,941
She needs someone to lean on right now.

328
00:17:48,442 --> 00:17:49,943
Thank you.

329
00:17:52,321 --> 00:17:56,325
[foreboding music playing]

330
00:17:56,408 --> 00:18:00,120
BUS HELD HOSTAGE
WITH JAPANESE TOURISTS EXPLODES

331
00:18:00,204 --> 00:18:01,914
Was this your plan, Manuel?

332
00:18:01,997 --> 00:18:03,916
It's great, isn't it?

333
00:18:03,999 --> 00:18:07,586
People are now angrier
with the government!

334
00:18:07,669 --> 00:18:10,506
Your brother wouldn't want you to do this.

335
00:18:12,549 --> 00:18:14,343
Who are you to say that?

336
00:18:14,426 --> 00:18:18,764
How would you know
what my brother would've wanted?

337
00:18:18,847 --> 00:18:20,140
You know, Manuel,

338
00:18:21,225 --> 00:18:25,521
this is the reason
why you and Napoleon fought so often.

339
00:18:25,604 --> 00:18:28,398
You kept doing stuff
without his permission.

340
00:18:29,066 --> 00:18:32,611
For example, what you did
in the medical mission…

341
00:18:32,694 --> 00:18:35,155
when you blew up M/V Doña Emilia,

342
00:18:35,239 --> 00:18:36,406
and so on!

343
00:18:38,242 --> 00:18:41,370
[tense music playing]

344
00:18:41,453 --> 00:18:43,288
[Napoleon] Why did you do that, Manuel?!

345
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:46,625
They almost caught us.

346
00:18:47,709 --> 00:18:49,837
They would have known about our operation

347
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:51,839
if I hadn't blown up the ship.

348
00:18:51,922 --> 00:18:53,924
But that's not what I wanted to happen.

349
00:18:56,135 --> 00:18:58,720
I'm just carrying out our plans.

350
00:18:58,804 --> 00:19:01,515
[in English] You bypassed
the chain of command!

351
00:19:02,307 --> 00:19:04,601
We got saved because of me.

352
00:19:04,685 --> 00:19:08,814
The authorities did not find
the weapons we were smuggling.

353
00:19:08,897 --> 00:19:11,859
You should be thanking me!

354
00:19:13,026 --> 00:19:15,279
[unsettling music playing]

355
00:19:21,243 --> 00:19:24,663
We are on the verge of success
because of me.

356
00:19:24,746 --> 00:19:27,040
Isn't that what matters?

357
00:19:27,124 --> 00:19:29,710
To bring order to the Republic!

358
00:19:29,793 --> 00:19:31,962
- Did you kill your brother?
- [scoffs]

359
00:19:33,964 --> 00:19:34,798
‪[dramatic sting]

360
00:19:36,758 --> 00:19:40,470
[music intensifies]

361
00:19:46,310 --> 00:19:51,648
What do you think matters more to me?

362
00:19:52,816 --> 00:19:56,403
Blood or duty?

363
00:19:57,070 --> 00:20:02,075
My family or my country?

364
00:20:03,243 --> 00:20:05,078
Hmm? [scoffs]

365
00:20:07,623 --> 00:20:10,083
- [door clicks open]
- You have lost it, Manuel.

366
00:20:10,167 --> 00:20:12,461
- [door clicks shut]
- You have lost it.

367
00:20:19,092 --> 00:20:20,677
Does anything hurt?

368
00:20:23,472 --> 00:20:25,015
So many people died.

369
00:20:25,098 --> 00:20:27,643
[morose music playing]

370
00:20:30,646 --> 00:20:33,190
All those innocent passengers
lost their lives.

371
00:20:35,901 --> 00:20:37,486
We couldn't save them.

372
00:20:40,030 --> 00:20:42,241
Don't blame yourself.

373
00:20:43,242 --> 00:20:45,494
You did everything you could.

374
00:20:46,078 --> 00:20:47,621
People need to be held accountable

375
00:20:48,372 --> 00:20:50,374
for what happened.

376
00:20:51,750 --> 00:20:54,461
Marcus and I will hunt them down.

377
00:20:55,629 --> 00:20:56,964
They will pay.

378
00:20:59,007 --> 00:21:01,176
[pensive music playing]

379
00:21:05,847 --> 00:21:07,516
[young Gabriel crying]

380
00:21:07,599 --> 00:21:09,768
Don't cry, Gabriel. I'll protect you.

381
00:21:09,851 --> 00:21:11,937
[sobs] Yes, Marcus!

382
00:21:12,688 --> 00:21:13,730
When…

383
00:21:15,190 --> 00:21:17,985
I lost consciousness,

384
00:21:18,902 --> 00:21:22,739
I think I had a dream.

385
00:21:24,241 --> 00:21:25,492
I don't know if…

386
00:21:26,618 --> 00:21:28,829
it's a memory from my childhood.

387
00:21:30,497 --> 00:21:31,748
What was it?

388
00:21:31,832 --> 00:21:33,166
In my dream…

389
00:21:36,962 --> 00:21:38,088
I had a brother.

390
00:21:38,755 --> 00:21:42,050
He was trying to save me.

391
00:21:44,011 --> 00:21:45,804
I don't know where we were.

392
00:21:45,887 --> 00:21:48,932
[stirring music playing]

393
00:21:49,016 --> 00:21:52,227
I don't really remember much about

394
00:21:52,311 --> 00:21:53,729
my real family.

395
00:21:58,025 --> 00:22:00,986
Was my dream a lost memory…

396
00:22:02,612 --> 00:22:04,281
that I'm finally remembering?

397
00:22:06,450 --> 00:22:09,953
I hope you regain all your memories,

398
00:22:10,037 --> 00:22:13,290
so you can find your real family.

399
00:22:14,166 --> 00:22:16,418
[gloomy music playing]

400
00:22:24,426 --> 00:22:26,053
I hope so, too, Doc.

401
00:22:27,054 --> 00:22:28,180
I hope so, too.

402
00:22:30,724 --> 00:22:31,892
But honestly,

403
00:22:31,975 --> 00:22:33,477
my whole life…

404
00:22:34,061 --> 00:22:35,604
I wasn't really searching for them.

405
00:22:37,481 --> 00:22:42,652
I was happy
with the family that took me in.

406
00:22:44,821 --> 00:22:45,947
But now,

407
00:22:46,990 --> 00:22:48,742
I want to know the truth.

408
00:22:49,868 --> 00:22:51,745
Who my real family is

409
00:22:52,579 --> 00:22:54,206
and what really happened.

410
00:22:56,833 --> 00:22:59,044
That's what I think about
all the time, too.

411
00:22:59,586 --> 00:23:00,796
[Teresa exhales]

412
00:23:02,631 --> 00:23:04,841
What if my son is still alive?

413
00:23:05,592 --> 00:23:07,469
How is he doing?

414
00:23:09,888 --> 00:23:12,099
I want to hug him so badly.

415
00:23:12,599 --> 00:23:15,227
[poignant music playing]

416
00:23:19,189 --> 00:23:20,232
[exhales]

417
00:23:49,261 --> 00:23:52,931
Those who truly control
the power in this country

418
00:23:53,014 --> 00:23:55,350
<i>are the Armed Forces.</i>

419
00:23:55,433 --> 00:23:57,602
We need intervention.

420
00:23:57,686 --> 00:24:00,939
[Madrigal] <i>Without it,</i>
<i>our country is going nowhere.</i>

421
00:24:01,022 --> 00:24:02,274
[Espina] <i>I can't rest.</i>

422
00:24:02,357 --> 00:24:03,233
We're waiting for Agent Angeles.

423
00:24:03,316 --> 00:24:04,568
Where is she?

424
00:24:04,651 --> 00:24:06,486
[Felix] <i>Lara, pick up!</i>

425
00:24:06,570 --> 00:24:08,321
[Felix] <i>Where are you?</i>

426
00:24:08,405 --> 00:24:10,448
I can only think of two reasons
she's not here.

427
00:24:10,532 --> 00:24:12,742
Either Lara's in danger

428
00:24:12,826 --> 00:24:15,579
or she blew up the bus
and has gone into hiding.

429
00:24:15,662 --> 00:24:19,457
If I tell him I was a member
of the syndicate,

430
00:24:19,541 --> 00:24:20,959
he will hate me.

431
00:24:21,042 --> 00:24:23,962
[Omar] <i>How long are you going</i>
<i>to hide this, Rahman?</i>

432
00:24:24,045 --> 00:24:25,213
<i>Especially from Jalil.</i>

433
00:24:25,297 --> 00:24:27,549
[Teresa] <i>I hope</i>
<i>you regain all your memories,</i>

434
00:24:27,632 --> 00:24:30,802
<i>so you can find your real family.</i>

435
00:24:30,886 --> 00:24:32,512
[Espina] <i>We're so close to solving this.</i>

436
00:24:32,596 --> 00:24:35,765
We're so close to achieving peace again.

437
00:24:35,849 --> 00:24:37,559
There's something I have to tell you.
